item.description:
One of the most damaging elements of traditional software development culture has been a strict allocation of duties between disciplines.
&ldquo;The designer draws some pictures and describes some functionality, the developers write code to make those pictures, the testers check that it works as expected.&rdquo;
That might work where projects aren&rsquo;t especially time constrained, and the business is comfortable making slow progress. Apply it to fast moving web development though and it causes numerous issues.
